Date: Tue, 2 Sep 2025 16:17:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] Implement comprehensive RCS capabilities with dynamic
 device adaptation
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

MAJOR ENHANCEMENT: Complete rewrite of RCS service with production-ready features

🔧 Device Capability Detection:
- Dual-SIM support and active SIM card status validation
- Comprehensive telephony manager availability checks
- Phone number registration validation with multiple identifiers
- Network connectivity type detection (WiFi, cellular, roaming)
- SMS/MMS functionality verification as RCS prerequisite

🌐 Network-Aware RCS Features:
- Dynamic feature enable/disable based on bandwidth and stability
- Intelligent fallback mechanisms for poor network conditions
- Enhanced carrier-specific configurations (Verizon, T-Mobile, AT&T, Sprint)
- Seamless network transition handling (WiFi ↔ cellular, roaming)
- Real-time network capability monitoring with callbacks

📊 Dynamic Capability Reporting:
- Real-time RCS capability updates based on device state changes
- Accurate feature availability reporting to Google Messages
- Intelligent capability caching with configurable refresh intervals
- Network-dependent feature limits (file sizes, group sizes, video duration)
- Carrier-aware configuration with automatic server selection

🛡️ Advanced Error Handling & Fallbacks:
- Graceful handling of unsupported carrier scenarios
- Comprehensive error classification with specific status codes
- Exponential backoff retry logic with configurable attempts
- Automatic SMS/MMS fallback when RCS unavailable
- Detailed error logging for troubleshooting

🏗️ Production-Ready Architecture:
- Thread-safe operations with ConcurrentHashMap callback management
- Memory-efficient caching with automatic cleanup
- Lifecycle-aware network monitoring with proper callback registration
- Comprehensive state persistence using SharedPreferences
- Industry-standard carrier detection with MCC/MNC validation

This implementation provides seamless RCS functionality that dynamically
adapts to real-world device conditions, matching Google Play Services
behavior while maintaining microG architectural standards.
